Four in the corner.

1036
01:17:52,147 --> 01:17:54,047
Twelve in the corner.

1037
01:17:54,649 --> 01:17:56,480
Three in the side.

1038
01:17:57,118 --> 01:17:58,915
Rack them.

1039
01:18:08,964 --> 01:18:11,023
Two in the corner.
Thirteen in the side.

1040
01:18:12,834 --> 01:18:14,495
Four in the side.

1041
01:18:14,703 --> 01:18:16,034
Twelve in the corner.

1042
01:18:18,974 --> 01:18:21,272
Fifteen in the side.

1043
01:18:24,012 --> 01:18:25,843
Eight in the corner.

1044
01:18:26,481 --> 01:18:28,346
Three in the corner.

1045
01:18:31,753 --> 01:18:33,687
Rack them.

1046
01:18:44,799 --> 01:18:46,460
Ten in the corner.

1047
01:19:03,151 --> 01:19:04,778
Eight, corner.

1048
01:19:06,921 --> 01:19:08,388
Five in the corner.

1049
01:19:12,560 --> 01:19:14,721
Fifteen in the side.

1050
01:19:16,698 --> 01:19:18,825
Eleven in the corner.

1051
01:19:21,403 --> 01:19:23,132
Rack them.

1052
01:19:31,713 --> 01:19:33,442
One in the corner.

1053
01:19:45,093 --> 01:19:46,993
Twelve in the corner.

1054
01:19:51,833 --> 01:19:55,234
Five in the corner.
Nine in the corner.

1055
01:19:58,606 --> 01:20:00,096
Fourteen in the corner.

1056
01:20:01,676 --> 01:20:03,166
Rack them.

1057
01:20:47,021 --> 01:20:47,988
Six, corner.

1058
01:20:55,730 --> 01:20:56,856
Seven, corner.

1059
01:20:57,766 --> 01:20:59,028
Ten, corner.

1060
01:21:06,608 --> 01:21:08,633
Fourteen in the corner.

1061
01:21:10,645 --> 01:21:14,103
Oh, eat Martian head, you're dead!

1062
01:21:17,685 --> 01:21:19,915
Two more points!

1063
01:21:22,056 --> 01:21:24,024
What's wrong?

1064
01:21:24,225 --> 01:21:26,125
I don't have a shot.

1065
01:21:32,734 --> 01:21:34,895
Well, what are you gonna do?

1066
01:21:35,103 --> 01:21:37,663
Make sure he doesn't have one either.

1067
01:22:01,462 --> 01:22:03,327
Three in the corner.

1068
01:22:03,531 --> 01:22:06,591
Oh, no, he can't make that, right?

1069
01:22:06,935 --> 01:22:08,527
Right?

1070
01:22:14,375 --> 01:22:16,036
- One more.
- Seven in the side.

1071
01:22:20,715 --> 01:22:22,842
That's the one we want.

1072
01:22:24,352 --> 01:22:26,684
Well, fair is fair, boys.

1073
01:22:26,888 --> 01:22:28,822
We'll just be running along.

1074
01:22:30,191 --> 01:22:33,524
- You don't mind if we count it, do you?
- Count it.

1075
01:22:36,331 --> 01:22:38,959
It's not that we don't trust you.

1076
01:22:58,586 --> 01:23:00,451
Bad idea, boys.

1077
01:23:00,655 --> 01:23:02,316
There seems to be
some kind of mix-up here.

1078
01:23:02,523 --> 01:23:03,888
Hopper, you know
anything about this?

1079
01:23:04,092 --> 01:23:05,059
What are you doing?

1080
01:23:05,260 --> 01:23:10,357
I know for a fact that when we walked
into this establishment and...

1081
01:23:10,865 --> 01:23:12,196
Shit.

1082
01:23:13,034 --> 01:23:14,001
Duck, Hopper!

1083
01:23:27,282 --> 01:23:28,681
Run.

1084
01:23:35,390 --> 01:23:36,914
Go!

1085
01:23:37,358 --> 01:23:39,258
- What the hell's wrong?
- Sometimes it takes time...

1086
01:23:39,460 --> 01:23:40,722
If you don't get this car started,

1087
01:23:40,929 --> 01:23:43,523
my dad's gonna have two more
holes to dig tomorrow. Let's go!

1088
01:24:29,644 --> 01:24:32,340
It's about time. What the hell
happened to you two?

1089
01:24:32,547 --> 01:24:33,946
Never mind, just get cleaned up.

1090
01:24:34,148 --> 01:24:36,343
You know what trouble
your mother's gone to?

1091
01:24:36,551 --> 01:24:39,782
You'd think you could be on time
for your own birthday, Henry.

1092
01:24:39,988 --> 01:24:41,353
- What happened?
- We had a run-in

1093
01:24:41,556 --> 01:24:44,150
- with the U.S. Navy.
- What? Where?

1094
01:24:44,359 --> 01:24:45,326
Up north.

1095
01:24:45,526 --> 01:24:48,256
- What were you doing up north?
- Playing pool.

1096
01:24:48,463 --> 01:24:50,397
- Actually, it was more like hustling pool.
- Nicky!

1097
01:24:50,598 --> 01:24:51,758
We needed money. A lot of money.

1098
01:24:51,966 --> 01:24:53,957
- Knock it off.
- What?!

1099
01:24:56,270 --> 01:24:58,465
- I know what you're doing.
- We're leaving here in a week.

1100
01:24:58,673 --> 01:24:59,731
- No.
- She's our last chance.

1101
01:24:59,941 --> 01:25:01,306
- Shut up!
- What am I supposed to do,

1102
01:25:01,509 --> 01:25:02,601
leave Sally here pregnant?

1103
01:25:02,810 --> 01:25:04,243
You son of a bitch!

1104
01:25:04,946 --> 01:25:05,913
What's going on?

1105
01:25:06,114 --> 01:25:08,674
Damn it, Caddie, I need $150!

1106
01:25:08,883 --> 01:25:11,374
You got some mouth, you know that?

1107
01:25:12,954 --> 01:25:16,355
I told you boys to get ready.
Come on now, speed it up.

1108
01:25:23,131 --> 01:25:25,122
Henry, what's the matter?

1109
01:25:32,273 --> 01:25:33,604
Will you sit down, Caddie?

1110
01:25:45,653 --> 01:25:48,121
Caddie, this is very hard for me.

1111
01:25:54,162 --> 01:25:57,654
The way I been raised, these
people just don't ask for things.

1112
01:26:02,603 --> 01:26:04,127
See...

1113
01:26:06,174 --> 01:26:08,335
...that girl you saw last night...

1114
01:26:08,543 --> 01:26:10,841
...Nicky got her pregnant.

1115
01:26:12,180 --> 01:26:14,341
And we gotta get her an abortion.

1116
01:26:14,882 --> 01:26:19,182
A clean abortion costs $150.

1117
01:26:19,387 --> 01:26:21,753
Nicky and I don't have
that kind of money.

1118
01:26:23,257 --> 01:26:25,157
You know what I'm saying?

1119
01:26:26,794 --> 01:26:28,284
I'm not sure.

1120
01:26:34,969 --> 01:26:36,834
Caddie...

1121
01:26:38,039 --> 01:26:39,404
...can you get us the money?

1122
01:26:39,607 --> 01:26:43,976
It's $150, and I'll make sure
you get every bit of it back.

1123
01:26:49,484 --> 01:26:51,782
I'll see what I can do.

1124
01:27:32,460 --> 01:27:34,451
Caddie, what are you doing here?

1125
01:27:37,498 --> 01:27:39,966
Why do you have my necklace?

1126
01:27:40,368 --> 01:27:42,859
You should have asked first.

1127
01:27:44,672 --> 01:27:47,505
Relax. It... It's okay, really.

1128
01:27:47,708 --> 01:27:49,801
Do you want to try it on?

1129
01:27:50,244 --> 01:27:51,871
Come on.

1130
01:27:54,215 --> 01:27:56,206
- Oh, no. I couldn't.
- Caddie.

1131
01:27:56,417 --> 01:27:57,679
What is the matter with you?

1132
01:27:57,885 --> 01:27:59,614
L... I want to go downstairs, I think.

1133
01:27:59,820 --> 01:28:02,084
Why are you so nervous?

1134
01:28:02,290 --> 01:28:04,520
Alice, I didn't come in here to try it on.

1135
01:28:04,725 --> 01:28:05,749
What are you talking about?

1136
01:28:05,960 --> 01:28:06,984
I came because I need money,

1137
01:28:07,195 --> 01:28:09,095
and the necklace is the only way
I could think of.

1138
01:28:09,564 --> 01:28:12,556
I don't understand. Why would
you do something like that?

1139
01:28:14,035 --> 01:28:15,468
Caddie, are you in trouble?

1140
01:28:16,103 --> 01:28:19,231
Oh, Alice. Alice.

1141
01:28:20,775 --> 01:28:23,471
I've made such a mess of things.

1142
01:28:23,844 --> 01:28:25,607
There is somebody who needs
something from me,

1143
01:28:25,813 --> 01:28:26,905
and he thinks I'm special,

1144
01:28:27,114 --> 01:28:29,582
and I just wanna give it to him.

1145
01:28:31,252 --> 01:28:32,685
I almost did a horrible thing,

1146
01:28:32,887 --> 01:28:36,584
but it's only because
I don't wanna let him down.

1147
01:28:39,760 --> 01:28:43,696
I wonder what it would be like
to be you sometimes.

1148
01:28:45,166 --> 01:28:47,031
I mean...

1149
01:28:48,402 --> 01:28:52,202
...I look around here, and everything
seems so much easier for you.

1150
01:28:53,674 --> 01:28:55,904
Not so much.

1151
01:29:01,349 --> 01:29:02,941
I'll get you the money.

1152
01:30:09,850 --> 01:30:12,842
I don't want you in there.

1153
01:30:37,044 --> 01:30:39,604
I guess they should be starting
in a few minutes.

1154
01:30:39,814 --> 01:30:41,873
They say it doesn't take too long.

1155
01:30:42,083 --> 01:30:44,813
There's another girl coming in at 11.

1156
01:30:45,186 --> 01:30:48,781
Boy, 150 bucks a shot,
that's some business, huh?

1157
01:30:48,989 --> 01:30:51,253
You should go in there
and hold her hand, Nicky.

1158
01:30:51,459 --> 01:30:53,893
She doesn't want me in there.

1159
01:31:34,201 --> 01:31:36,533
Oh, I'm sick.

1160
01:33:13,467 --> 01:33:15,560
<i>- the exact location
from which I'm speaking.</i>

1161
01:33:15,769 --> 01:33:17,896
<i>Off to my left, far away
in the distance,</i>

1162
01:33:18,105 --> 01:33:20,767
<i>I can see just that faint, red,
angry snap</i>

1163
01:33:20,975 --> 01:33:25,776
<i>of antiaircraft bursts
against a steel-blue sky.</i>

1164
01:33:38,959 --> 01:33:41,086
- Nicky.
- Huh?

1165
01:33:41,295 --> 01:33:43,661
- Will you stop, please?
- Huh?

1166
01:33:43,864 --> 01:33:45,798
Will you stop, please?
Stop the car, please?

1167
01:33:46,033 --> 01:33:47,728
- What's the matter, Caddie?
- I wanna get out.

1168
01:33:47,935 --> 01:33:50,233
Cad, it's only a few more blocks.

1169
01:33:50,437 --> 01:33:52,735
Would you stop the damn car?!

1170
01:34:00,981 --> 01:34:04,109
- Cad. Caddie, where you going?
- Home.

1171
01:34:04,318 --> 01:34:07,287
- I'll walk you.
- No, I don't want you to walk me.

1172
01:34:07,488 --> 01:34:09,149
I know what you're thinking.

1173
01:34:09,356 --> 01:34:12,189
You're thinking that could've been you
in there. Well, you're wrong, Caddie.

1174
01:34:12,393 --> 01:34:14,987
I'd never take you to a place
like that, I'd marry you.

1175
01:34:15,195 --> 01:34:17,288
Did you hear what I said?
I'd marry you.

1176
01:34:17,498 --> 01:34:20,990
Oh, well, what makes you think
I'd marry you?

1177
01:34:21,635 --> 01:34:23,000
- Get back in the car.
- No.

1178
01:34:23,203 --> 01:34:25,034
- Get back in the goddamn car.
- Let go of my arm.

1179
01:34:25,239 --> 01:34:26,433
Oh, I'm sorry.

1180
01:34:27,041 --> 01:34:30,272
I didn't know you were gonna
end up running into that place.

1181
01:34:32,212 --> 01:34:34,180
What do you want from me?

1182
01:34:35,282 --> 01:34:37,443
I don't want anything from you.

1183
01:34:37,851 --> 01:34:40,376
Hey, I'm talking to you.

1184
01:34:41,088 --> 01:34:43,022
It's the money, right?

1185
01:34:44,358 --> 01:34:46,918
You think I took advantage of you
because I asked you for that money.

1186
01:34:47,127 --> 01:34:50,460
Well, Caddie, we needed that money,
and you're the only rich person I know.

1187
01:34:51,332 --> 01:34:53,960
You are such an idiot.

1188
01:34:54,168 --> 01:34:56,636
I'm not rich.

1189
01:34:56,837 --> 01:35:00,136
- What?
- I'm not rich.

1190
01:35:00,341 --> 01:35:01,808
What are you talking about?

1191
01:35:02,009 --> 01:35:05,137
Yes, I live in that house on the hill.
Do you know why I live in that house?

1192
01:35:05,346 --> 01:35:07,109
Because my mother
works in that house.

1193
01:35:07,314 --> 01:35:08,838
My mom is a maid.

1194
01:35:09,049 --> 01:35:10,949
She's a maid in that house.

1195
01:35:11,151 --> 01:35:13,244
Goddamn you!

1196
01:35:13,454 --> 01:35:15,684
I tried to tell you
about a million times.

1197
01:35:15,889 --> 01:35:19,222
But you are so pleased
with your little girl on the hill

1198
01:35:19,426 --> 01:35:22,327
that I didn't wanna disappoint you.

1199
01:35:31,672 --> 01:35:33,299
Just leave me alone.

1200
01:35:33,507 --> 01:35:35,498
Leave me alone.

1201
01:35:42,383 --> 01:35:44,112
Hop, you coming?

1202
01:35:44,985 --> 01:35:46,452
Hop.

1203
01:36:01,035 --> 01:36:02,297
What are you doing?

1204
01:36:02,503 --> 01:36:06,030
This is my old man's car,
you crazy son of a bitch.

1205
01:36:06,240 --> 01:36:07,639
What the hell's the matter with you?

1206
01:36:07,841 --> 01:36:09,741
You, Nicky, you're
what's the matter with me.

1207
01:36:09,943 --> 01:36:11,308
You're always making your life
a mess,

1208
01:36:11,512 --> 01:36:12,979
and I'm always getting you out of it.

1209
01:36:13,180 --> 01:36:15,410
- Hey, it's over. It's all fixed.
- Shut up. Shut up.

1210
01:36:16,684 --> 01:36:18,982
Sally could've died tonight, Nicky.
That ever cross your mind?

1211
01:36:19,186 --> 01:36:21,279
But she didn't.

1212
01:36:22,656 --> 01:36:25,557
Jesus, you just don't get it, do you?

1213
01:36:26,026 --> 01:36:28,392
And then you get her mixed up in it.

1214
01:36:31,865 --> 01:36:34,993
I'm sick of you messing up
my life, Nicky.

1215
01:36:36,570 --> 01:36:38,197
I'm sick of it.

1216
01:36:43,877 --> 01:36:46,971
You didn't even open the door
for her, Nicky.

1217
01:36:48,215 --> 01:36:49,409
Girl just had an abortion,

1218
01:36:49,616 --> 01:36:52,813
you can't even get out of the car
and open the door for her.

1219
01:37:22,483 --> 01:37:24,474
Damn cold for February.

1220
01:37:24,685 --> 01:37:25,811
Laid a bed of these last night.

1221
01:37:26,019 --> 01:37:28,214
This morning, the ground
was still like rock.

1222
01:37:28,422 --> 01:37:30,219
I don't know what it is.

1223
01:37:31,825 --> 01:37:35,659
Your mom says Nicky's been by
the house three times this past week.

1224
01:37:39,466 --> 01:37:41,559
Well, you know your own mind.

1225
01:37:41,769 --> 01:37:45,205
Just seems you two could use
each other's company about now.

1226
01:37:49,309 --> 01:37:51,675
You know, for a time,
right after his mom died,

1227
01:37:51,879 --> 01:37:54,347
Nicky brought flowers here
every day.

1228
01:37:54,548 --> 01:37:56,948
Come after school, just sit there.

1229
01:37:57,151 --> 01:38:00,518
Be so tired, I'd have to carry him
home on my shoulders.

1230
01:38:01,522 --> 01:38:02,648
Did you know that?

1231
01:38:04,458 --> 01:38:07,450
Yeah, well, it was a long time ago.

1232
01:38:16,737 --> 01:38:19,365
Damn cold for February.

1233
01:38:19,573 --> 01:38:20,972
Yeah.

1234
01:39:10,858 --> 01:39:12,553
How you doing?

1235
01:39:14,194 --> 01:39:17,186
- Okay. You?
- Okay.

1236
01:39:19,600 --> 01:39:22,797
- Thursday's the big day, huh?
- Yeah, I guess so.

1237
01:39:27,007 --> 01:39:27,996
You ready?

1238
01:39:28,208 --> 01:39:29,971
- You bet.
- Me too.

1239
01:39:35,515 --> 01:39:38,643
- I went by and I saw Sally.
- Yeah?

1240
01:39:39,119 --> 01:39:42,646
Just to see how she was doing
and everything, you know.

1241
01:39:42,856 --> 01:39:44,585
- How is she?
- She's good.

1242
01:39:44,791 --> 01:39:46,281
That's good.

1243
01:39:49,596 --> 01:39:52,394
You know what she said to me
just before I left?

1244
01:39:54,001 --> 01:39:56,731
She said,
"Take care of yourself, Nick. "

1245
01:39:57,671 --> 01:39:59,502
Can you beat that?

1246
01:40:11,718 --> 01:40:14,209
We gotta stick together, Nicky.

1247
01:40:15,188 --> 01:40:17,179
We gotta stick together.

1248
01:40:21,094 --> 01:40:22,493
Yeah.

1249
01:40:25,332 --> 01:40:26,822
Yeah.

1250
01:42:08,435 --> 01:42:10,562
Why don't you try them on.

1251
01:42:30,323 --> 01:42:32,484
I already know they fit.

1252
01:42:49,142 --> 01:42:51,110
I love you, Caddie.

1253
01:42:53,213 --> 01:42:55,408
I love you, Henry.

1254
01:43:33,153 --> 01:43:34,552
Don't cry, Mom.

1255
01:43:34,754 --> 01:43:36,278
I'm not crying.

1256
01:43:36,490 --> 01:43:38,754
You come back and play for me.

1257
01:43:38,959 --> 01:43:40,551
Board!

1258
01:43:44,898 --> 01:43:47,594
- Keep your eyes peeled.
- I will, Dad.

1259
01:43:50,504 --> 01:43:53,268
- You too, Nicky.
- I will, sir.

1260
01:43:55,609 --> 01:43:56,667
Take care.

1261
01:43:58,778 --> 01:44:01,338
I brought something for you.

1262
01:44:04,151 --> 01:44:06,210
It's for your wallet.

1263
01:44:10,490 --> 01:44:12,651
All aboard.

1264
01:44:21,735 --> 01:44:23,134
Board.

1265
01:44:23,336 --> 01:44:25,201
